  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The book \"Building Collaborative Governance in Times of Uncertainty,\" published by Leuven University Press in 2023, demonstrates a strong inclination towards scholarly uptake, evidenced by a significant rate of citations. This indicates its potential influence in the academic discourse surrounding governance structures in uncertain environments.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Building Collaborative Governance in Times of Uncertainty\" is a timely exploration of governance mechanisms during unpredictable times. Published by Leuven University Press in 2023, the work has garnered a substantial academic footprint, as indicated by its citation count, which reflects a growing interest in the subject matter among researchers. With 12 citations, this book signifies a notable engagement with the complexities of collaborative governance.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">The emphasis on sustainability and policy relevance further enhances the book's impact, aligning it with contemporary objectives such as the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs). Specifically, the work addresses one SDG, showcasing its relevance not only in academic discussions but also in practical policy-making contexts.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">Additionally, the inferred roles suggest that there is a commercial linkage, further implying a broader interest from various stakeholders in the themes explored within the book. Such indicators point to its dual appeal – engaging both academic audiences and practitioners committed to effective governance practices.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">While current metrics indicate no public discourse on platforms like Wikipedia or Reddit, the scholarly uptake demonstrates the potential for future discussions as the academic community continues to unpack the themes presented in \"Building Collaborative Governance in Times of Uncertainty.\" This reflects the evolving nature of collaborative governance and highlights its critical importance in contemporary studies, setting a foundation for further research and dialogue in the field.</p>",
